# Auth Rules

## Flow

OTP-based login only — no passwords. No password reset, no email/password pair.

## Token Lifecycle

| Token | TTL | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Access | 15 min | Short-lived, client memory |
| Refresh | 7 days | Rotation on every use |

Every JWT includes a `jti` claim (UUID v4). Refresh token is invalidated immediately on use — issue a new pair.

## Redis Blocklist

Revoked tokens stored in Redis keyed by `jti`. TTL = remaining token lifetime — never store longer than the token would have been valid.

```typescript
// Revoke
const ttlMs = expiresAt - Date.now();
await redis.set(`blocklist:${jti}`, '1', 'PX', ttlMs);

// Verify in AuthGuard — reject before any business logic
const blocked = await redis.exists(`blocklist:${jti}`);
if (blocked) throw new UnauthorizedException({ code: 'TOKEN_REVOKED' });
```

## Guards — Compose, Never Inline

Apply guards via `@UseGuards()` decorators. Never write manual JWT or role checks inside controller method bodies.

```typescript
// BAD — manual role check in controller
if (req.user.role !== 'provider') throw new ForbiddenException();

// GOOD — composed guard decorators
@UseGuards(AuthGuard, RolesGuard)
@Roles('provider')
@Get('dashboard')
getDashboard(): Promise<DashboardDto> { ... }
```

## OTP Rate Limiting

Rate-limit OTP request endpoints per phone number via Redis. Common abuse vector on mobile auth.

```typescript
const key = `otp_rate:${phoneNumber}`;
const count = await redis.incr(key);
if (count === 1) await redis.expire(key, 60); // 60-second window
if (count > 3) throw new TooManyRequestsException({ code: 'OTP_RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED' });
```
